This suggests either the button wasn't visible or accessible at that moment, or the BID might have changed. Looking at the current page's accessibility tree, I can see that I'm already on a page that shows 'Improve installation documentation (#677)' in the title, which indicates that the issue has actually been created successfully. The page shows details of the newly created issue including the title and description I entered earlier. The issue is marked as 'Open' and it shows it was created 'just now' by 'Byte Blaze'. This confirms that the issue creation was successful despite the error message I received. Since the goal was to create a new issue for the autojump project, and that has been accomplished (issue #677 has been created), I should inform the user of the success.
